Acibadem, Akfen, Migros, Ulker: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-04-11T06:44:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/acibadem-akfen-migros-ulker-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in Turkey. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  fell 1,397.21, or
2 percent, to 68,093.26 yesterday.  Acibadem Saglik Hizmetleri & Ticaret AS (ACIBD TI): The
Turkish hospital chain said its full-year net income declined to
11.5 million liras ($7.6 million) from 17.9 million liras in
2009, according to a statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange 
after the market closed on April 8. Acibadem Saglik rose 1.15
liras, of 7.7 percent, to 16 liras.  Akfen Holding AS (AKFEN)  : The Turkish builder said full-
year net income dropped to 71.8 million liras from 149.9 million
liras in 2009, in a statement to the bourse after the market
closed on April 8. Akfen gained 35 kurus, or 3.2 percent, to
11.3 liras.  Migros Ticaret AS (MGROS)  : The Turkish supermarket chain
said its owner  BC Partners  Holdings Ltd. set a price of 25 liras
per share for the sale of a 17.4 percent stake in Migros,
valuing the stake at 775 million liras. BC Partners will sell
the 31 million Migros shares via a “placement agreement” with
JPMorgan Chase & Co. and Merrill Lynch & Co., Migros said in a
filing with the bourse after markets closed on April 8. Migros
dropped 1 lira, or 3 percent, to 32.5 liras.  Ulker Biskuvi Sanayi AS (ULKER)  : The owner of Godiva
chocolates said net income last year jumped to 184.8 million
liras from 102.9 million liras in 2009, according to a statement
to the bourse after markets closed on April 8. The profit
exceeded an average estimate of 93.5 million liras in a
Bloomberg survey of four analysts. Ulker fell 4 kurus, or 0.7
percent, to 5.76 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
